        <blockquote>
          <div align="left">
            <ul>
              <li><font size="+1" color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000"><font color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000">Animated
                        Gifs - We've got preliminary support for loading
                        gif animations in Howler</font></font></font></font></li>
              <li><font size="+1" color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000"><font color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000">Committed a
                        270 word spelling library to the API.&nbsp; It's
                        a start. Can you guess where that's going?</font></font></font></font></li>
              <li><font size="+1" color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000"><font color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000">Added an API
                        for working with GIF animations and additional
                        support for wide strings.</font></font></font></font></li>
              <li><font size="+1" color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000"><font color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000">The OBJ
                        loader is now 64 bit - try the <a moz-do-not-send="true" href="2024/index.html#try">free standalone
                          version</a></font></font></font></font></li>
              <li><font size="+1" color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000"><font color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000">In the
                        geometry renderer, you can now open a file in
                        its default program(such as 3D Builder, 3D
                        Viewer, 3D Paint,... whatever you've configured
                        it to be on your PC)&nbsp; or also with Notepad.
                        This helps in quickly checking details and
                        perhaps fixing possible issues in the materials
                        or obj files.</font></font></font></font></li>
              <li><font size="+1" color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000"><font color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000">Stored
                        animations now show the frame number (!)</font></font></font></font></li>
              <li><font size="+1" color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000"><font color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000">Analytical
                        upscale now warns if its going to close an
                        animation. </font></font></font></font></li>
              <li><font size="+1" color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000"><font color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000">faster
                        clipmaps and some general optimization</font></font></font></font></li>
              <li><font size="+1" color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000"><font color="#ff0000"><font color="#000000">The mip-map
                        seam problem is solved. (yay me!)</font></font></font></font></li>

                                                          are Here! +</b></font></font></font><font face="Verdana"><font face="Verdana"><font size="+3"><b>+</b></font></font></font><font face="Verdana"><font face="Verdana"><font size="+3"><b>+</b></font></font></font><font face="Verdana"><font face="Verdana"><font size="+3"><b>+</b></font></font></font><br>

                                                          <font size="+1"><a href="dogwaffle/newsletter/188-happy-spooky-Halloween/index.html"><img moz-do-not-send="true" src="2023/pics/illustration-by-Dan-Ritchie_800.jpg" alt="" width="669" height="435" border="0"></a><br>

                                                          <blockquote><i><b>
                                                          </b>This was
                                                          painted by Dan
                                                          Ritchie with
                                                          PD Howler. <br>
                                                          The image
                                                          features
                                                          Silver
                                                          Squirrel and
                                                          Pillow
                                                          Rabbit.&nbsp;
                                                          Silver added
                                                          Pillow to his
                                                          family as a
                                                          service animal
                                                          to help him
                                                          with a
                                                          disability.&nbsp;
                                                          The deer are
                                                          Margaret
                                                          Mayflower and
                                                          Milton
                                                          Meadows.&nbsp;
                                                          Margaret is an
                                                          itinerant
                                                          judge and
                                                          member of the
                                                          Court of
                                                          Animals.&nbsp;
                                                          Milton agreed
                                                          to assist her
                                                          after she was
                                                          injured at the
                                                          Battle of the
                                                          Flee Market in
                                                          "Sky Full of
                                                          Rabbits."&nbsp;
                                                          Together they
                                                          are on their
                                                          way to Deer
                                                          City, a.k.a
                                                          The Princedom
                                                          of the Hill,
                                                          which is also
                                                          the name of
                                                          the book.<b> </b></i><br>
                                                          <i><b> <br>
                                                          Learn more
                                                          about Silver
                                                          Squirrel here
                                                          &gt;&gt;&gt;&nbsp;

















































                                                          </b></i><a moz-do-not-send="true" href="https://www.pdhowler.com/Silver.htm"><i><b>https://www.pdhowler.com/Silver.htm</b></i></a></blockquote>

                                                          you!.....
